ggbnec_data.default

Source: R/autoplot.R
ggbnec_data.default.Rd

Creates the data.frame that feeds into the plotting function ggbnec.

# S3 method for default
ggbnec_data(x, add_nec = TRUE, add_ecx = FALSE, ...)

Arguments

x

An object of class bayesnecfit, as returned by function bnec.
add_nec

Should NEC values be added to the plot? Defaults to TRUE.
add_ecx

Should ECx values be added to the plot? Defaults to FALSE.
...

Additional arguments to be passed to ecx. By default, function ecx returns EC10.

Value

A data.frame.

Examples

# \donttest{
library(bayesnec)
data(manec_example)

ggbnec_data(manec_example)
